{"questionId":"9068079","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">An equation for the combustion of propane is given below.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>8</sub>(g) + 5O<sub>2</sub>(g)&nbsp;<img src=\"__IMG__/ca969f9bcf69ab85fc1ae01a5df9e34413ad9fff.png\">3CO<sub>2</sub>(g) + 4H<sub>2</sub>O(g)</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Predict, giving a reason, whether the entropy change, </span><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∆</mo><msup><mi>S</mi><mo>⦵</mo></msup></math><span class=\"fontstyle0\">, for this reaction is negative or positive.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>positive <em><strong>AND</strong> </em>more moles «of gas» in products ✔</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9068079","referenceCode":"20N.2.hl.TZ0.c","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Predict, giving a reason, whether the entropy change, ∆S⦵, for this reaction is negative or positive.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 15: Energetics/thermochemistry","15.2 Entropy and spontaneity","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 15: Energetics/thermochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}